                  rdfs:label "cubic equivalency assertion"@en ;
                  skos:definition """cubic equivalency assertion is a symmetry equivalency assertion which is used to infer crystallographic equivalence between single crystallographic direction /plane and family of directions/planes under the cubic crystal symmetry.
In particular, it considers <100>, <110>, and <111> families of crystallographic directions, as well as {100}, {110}, {111} families of crystallographic planes"""@en .


